description:
Gavin DeGraw

Gavin DeGraw first broke through with the 2003 release of his debut album, Chariot, which sold more than a million copies and produced three hit singles in "I Don't Want to Be," "Follow Through" and the title track. His self-titled sophomore album debuted at #1 on the digital sales chart and #7 on Billboard's Top 200 in 2008, spawning the singles, "In Love with a Girl" and the gold "We Belong Together." He released his third solo album, Sweeter, in September 2011, featuring the chart-topping, double-platinum Hot AC and Top 10 pop hit, "Not Over You," co-written with OneRepublic's Ryan Tedder. His fourth studio album, Make a Move, came out last October. Gavin recently received his first Grammy nomination for "We Both Know," a song he co-wrote and sang with Colbie Caillat for last year's film, Safe Haven. Next month, DeGraw embarks on the first leg of a headlining U.S. tour and will open a string of dates for Billy Joel, including two shows at New York's Madison Square Garden March 21 and April 1.
